The right side of the equation has a degree of 6 (the highest power of *x* is 6).  The polynomial $(x^2 - 1)$ has a degree of 2.  

To get a degree of 6 on the right side, the polynomial *f(x)* must have a degree of 4.

So the answer is:

\begin{align*}
\boxed{4}
\end{align*}

